6 An Act relating to professions and occupations;
amending 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1354, as amended by
7 Section 1, Chapter 66, O.S.L. 2023 (59 O.S. Supp.
2024, Section 1354), which relates to the State Board
8 of Examiners of Psychologists; extending sunset date;
updating statutory language; providing an effective
9 date; and declaring an emergency.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 59 O.S. 2021, Section 1354, as
14 amended by Section 1, Chapter 66, O.S.L. 2023 (59 O.S. Supp. 2024,
15 Section 1354), is amended to read as follows:
16 Section 1354. There is hereby re-created, to continue until
17 July 1, 2025 July 1, 2028, pursuant to the provisions of the
18 Oklahoma Sunset Law, the State Board of Examiners of Psychologists.
19 The Board shall administer the provisions of the Psychologists
20 Licensing Act. The Board shall consist of seven (7) members
21 appointed by the Governor. Five members shall be psychologists from
22 various areas in psychology and two members shall be lay persons.
23 At the expiration of the term of each Board member who is a
24 psychologist, the Governor shall appoint a successor from a list of
ENGR. S. B. NO. 395 Page 1
1 ten licensed psychologists which is provided by the Oklahoma State
2 Psychological Association. Members shall serve for a term of four
3 (4) years and until a successor is appointed and qualified. Before
4 entering upon the duties of office, each member of the Board shall
5 take the constitutional oath of office and file it with the
6 Secretary of State.
7 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
8 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
9 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
10 declared to exist, by reason whereof this act shall take effect and
11 be in full force from and after its passage and approval.
12 Passed the Senate the 25th day of March, 2025.
